{Zenón Franco is a Grandmaster from Paraguay, now living in Spain. He
represented Paraguay, on top board, in seven Chess Olympiads, and won
individual gold medals at Lucerne 1982 and Novi Sad 1990. He's an experienced
trainer and has written numerous books on chess.} 1. -- {Also by the Author:
Anand: Move by Move; Rubinstein: Move by Move; Spassky: Move by Move; Test
Your Chess.} *

